'''委內瑞拉示威'''是發生在2014年至今，[[委內瑞拉|委內瑞拉]]一系列的政治示威抗議活動，反對總統[[尼古拉斯·馬杜羅|尼古拉斯·馬杜羅]]領導的執政黨[[委內瑞拉統一社會主義黨|委內瑞拉統一社會主義黨]]政府。抗議活動理由包括高暴力犯罪率、[[委內瑞拉物資短缺|基本物資不足]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Venezuela's Maduro says 2013 annual inflation was 56.2 pct|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/12/30/venezuela-inflation-annual-idUSL2N0K90V020131230|accessdate=19 January 2014|newspaper=Reuters|date=30 December 2013|archive-date=2015-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016050958/http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/12/30/venezuela-inflation-annual-idUSL2N0K90V020131230|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Venezuela Inflation Hits 16-Year High as Shortages Rise|url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-07/venezuela-inflation-hits-16-year-high-as-shortages-rise.html|accessdate=16 February 2014|newspaper=Bloomberg|date=7 November 2013|archive-date=2014-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222160511/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-07/venezuela-inflation-hits-16-year-high-as-shortages-rise.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>反对者把造成这些情况的源头直接指向委内瑞拉政府的经济政策，如严格的价格管制。这些政策导致了国内相比世界其他地方有着高通货膨胀率<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/rankorder/2092rank.html|title=Inflation rate (consumer prices)|work=[[CIA_World_Factbook|CIA World Factbook]]|accessdate=26 February 2014|archive-date=2017-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907162535/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/rankorder/2092rank.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="economist.com">{{cite news|url=http://www.economist.com/node/21526365|accessdate=23 February 2014|title=Venezuela’s economy: Medieval policies|work=[[The_Economist|The Economist]]|archive-date=2018-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613134318/https://www.economist.com/node/21526365|dead-url=no}}</ref>以及食品和其他商品的严重短缺。<ref name="economist.com"/>而马杜罗总统指责反对他的人的目的是发动“经济战”，特别指责乃资本主义的干涉。<ref name="Edition.cnn.com">{{cite web |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2013/11/20/world/americas/venezuela-economy-decree-powers/ |title=Decree powers widen Venezuelan president's economic war - CNN.com |publisher=Edition.cnn.com |date=20 November 2013 |accessdate=21 February 2014 |archive-date=2014-02-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140226130319/http://edition.cnn.com/2013/11/20/world/americas/venezuela-economy-decree-powers/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>因此，全国各地的城市几乎都发生了反对总统的抗议活动，这些抗议活动已发生冲突并导致多人被逮捕、受伤以及死亡。

早期的抗议犯罪活动发生于2014年1月，前女演员及[[委内瑞拉小姐|委内瑞拉小姐]]得主[[莫尼卡·斯皮尔·莫茨|莫尼卡·斯皮尔·莫茨]]以及她丈夫于2014年1月6日在路边遭遇抢劫并被杀害，而他们五六岁大的女儿在车中幸免于难。<ref name=MostDangerous>{{cite web |url=http://www.channel4.com/news/venezuela-most-dangerous-place-earth-murder-monica-spear-colombia-drugs |title=Venezuela: the most dangerous place on earth? – Channel 4 News |publisher=Channel4.com |date=8 January 2014 |accessdate=21 February 2014 |archive-date=2014-02-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228154310/http://www.channel4.com/news/venezuela-most-dangerous-place-earth-murder-monica-spear-colombia-drugs |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=WhatTheHeck>{{cite web |url=http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-02-18/what-the-heck-is-going-on-in-venezuela-could-the-maduro-regime-fall |title=What the Heck Is Going on in Venezuela? (Could the Maduro Regime Fall?) |publisher=Businessweek |date= |accessdate=21 February 2014 |archive-date=2014-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301184508/http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-02-18/what-the-heck-is-going-on-in-venezuela-could-the-maduro-regime-fall |dead-url=no }}</ref>另一宗犯罪发生于2月，其中一个年轻的女大学生在[[聖克里斯托瓦爾_(塔奇拉州)|聖克里斯托瓦爾]]大学校园中遭遇强奸未遂，导致学生们的抗议运动；<ref name=AttemptedRape/>这些抗议活动扩大到其他城市，反对派则趁此时混入进抗议队伍。<ref name= AttemptedRape/>学生的抗议活动恰逢1814年2月12日{{link-en|委内瑞拉独立战争|Venezuelan War of Independence}}的{{link-en|拉维多利亚战役 (1812)|Battle of La Victoria (1812)|拉维多利亚战役}}纪念日期间，当时独立武装势力因为兵力不足而征召了大量在校学生。这个日期也被称为全国青年日。抗议活动的持续被人称作“委内瑞拉之春”，这个名称参考了知名的[[阿拉伯之春|阿拉伯之春]]运动。<ref name="Indendent Spring">{{Cite web |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/a-venezuelan-spring-three-killed-as-armed-vigilantes-on-motorcycles-attack-antigovernment-protesters-9124935.html |title=A Venezuelan Spring? Three killed as armed vigilantes on motorcycles attack anti-government protesters |accessdate=2014-03-02 |archive-date=2014-03-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302115050/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/a-venezuelan-spring-three-killed-as-armed-vigilantes-on-motorcycles-attack-antigovernment-protesters-9124935.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="abruzzo Spring">{{Cite web |url=http://www.abruzzo24ore.tv/news/Venezuela-Continuano-le-manifestazioni-di-protesta/134703.htm |title=Venezuela: Continuano le manifestazioni di protesta |accessdate=2014-03-02 |archive-date=2014-02-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223231823/http://www.abruzzo24ore.tv/news/Venezuela-Continuano-le-manifestazioni-di-protesta/134703.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://oglobo.globo.com/mundo/a-venezuela-amanhece-com-outra-realidade-diz-capriles-3957447 |title=-{‘A Venezuela amanhece com outra realidade’}-, diz Capriles |accessdate=2014-03-02 |archive-date=2014-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303080524/http://oglobo.globo.com/mundo/a-venezuela-amanhece-com-outra-realidade-diz-capriles-3957447 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="El Mundo Spring">{{cite news|last=Montaner|first=Gina|title=La Primavera Venezolana|url=http://www.elmundo.es/internacional/2014/02/17/530248ef22601d0f028b457c.html|accessdate=26 February 2014|newspaper=El Mundo (Spain)|date=18 February 2014|archive-date=2014-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140306210638/http://www.elmundo.es/internacional/2014/02/17/530248ef22601d0f028b457c.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2014年3月3日[[联合国秘书长|联合国秘书长]][[潘基文|潘基文]]和委内瑞拉外长{{link-en|埃利亚斯·豪阿|Elias Jaua}}计划于日内瓦召开会议。<ref>Associated Press. March 2, 2014. [http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/chief-meet-venezuelas-foreign-minister-22735619 UN Chief to Meet Venezuela's Foreign Minister] {{Wayback|url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/chief-meet-venezuelas-foreign-minister-22735619 |date=20140304112623 }}. ''ABC News.'' Retrieved: 2 March 2014.</ref>豪阿将向[[联合国人权理事会|联合国人权理事会]]解释政府的行动。在此之后，[[联合国|联合国]]秘书长潘基文发表一份声明称“我重申，希望看到当前紧张局势缓解并在必要情况下进行有意义的对话。”<ref>March 3, 2014. [http://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-26424779 UN's Ban Ki-moon urges Venezuela to hear protesters' demands] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-26424779 |date=20140327201743 }}. ''BBC News.'' Retrieved: 7 March 2014.</ref>

委内瑞拉主要由公众舆论和消费者参与的组织“Datos”在2月28日和3月2日之间对主要城市的800名受访者进行了调查。<ref>{{cite news|title=Datos: 64% de acuerdo con salir de este gobierno lo antes posible, de forma constitucional (encuesta)|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2014/03/16/datos-64-de-acuerdo-con-salir-de-este-gobierno-lo-antes-posible-de-forma-constitucional-encuesta/|accessdate=16 March 2014|newspaper=La Patilla|date=16 March 2014|archive-date=2014-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140320101037/http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2014/03/16/datos-64-de-acuerdo-con-salir-de-este-gobierno-lo-antes-posible-de-forma-constitucional-encuesta/|dead-url=no}}</ref>Datos调查发现，超过半数的受访者指责问题是马杜罗政府造成的。64％的人认为政府应该尽快从宪法最高权力中离开。对于目前的政治局势，43.7％的人支持反对派，而支持政府的人则为27.1％。当被问及全国大局时，27.2％认为持正面态度，而72.0％的人认为国内情况在过去的一年中愈发恶劣。<ref name=DATOScaracas>{{cite news|title=87% de los venezolanos cree que el Gobierno debe rectificar sus políticas|url=http://diariodecaracas.com/politica/87-los-venezolanos-cree-que-el-gobierno-debe-rectificar-sus-politicas|accessdate=16 March 2014|newspaper=El Diario de Caracas|date=16 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140320063220/http://diariodecaracas.com/politica/87-los-venezolanos-cree-que-el-gobierno-debe-rectificar-sus-politicas|archive-date=2014-03-20|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Encuesta Datos: 72% cree que las cosas van mal en el país (+Estudio)|url=http://www.venezuelaaldia.com/2014/03/encuesta-datos-72-cree-que-las-cosas-van-mal-en-el-pais-estudio/|accessdate=16 March 2014|newspaper=Venezuela Al Dia|date=16 March 2014|archive-date=2014-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140319082318/http://www.venezuelaaldia.com/2014/03/encuesta-datos-72-cree-que-las-cosas-van-mal-en-el-pais-estudio/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=DatosDATA>{{cite web|title=Datos Presentación Clima País_Feb 2014|url=http://www.scribd.com/doc/212694194/Datos-Presentacion-Clima-Pais-Feb-2014|publisher=Datos|accessdate=16 March 2014|archive-date=2014-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140321043615/http://www.scribd.com/doc/212694194/Datos-Presentacion-Clima-Pais-Feb-2014|dead-url=no}}</ref>据[[蓋洛普_(公司)|盖洛普]]的调查表明，委内瑞拉52％的人不赞成马杜罗总统，赞成的为34％，对政府的信心下降至历史最低的39％。<ref name=GALLUPven>{{cite web|title=Venezuelans Saw Political Instability Before Protests|url=http://www.gallup.com/poll/167663/venezuelans-saw-political-instability-protests.aspx|publisher=Gallup|accessdate=18 March 2014|archive-date=2014-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140318092847/http://www.gallup.com/poll/167663/venezuelans-saw-political-instability-protests.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==背景==
[[File:PROTEST_REASONS_sign.jpg|250px]]
抗議暴力的示威活动始于2014年1月<ref name=MostDangerous/>，並且持續。那时反對派領袖、前总统候选人[[恩里克·卡普利莱斯·拉东斯基|恩里克·卡普利莱斯·拉东斯基]]与马杜罗总统握手，这个“手势使他失去支持，並推動”另一反对派领导人[[萊奧波爾多·洛佩斯|莱奥波尔多·洛佩斯·门多萨]]走上前台。<ref name=WhatTheHeck/>据美联社报道，抗议活动在委内瑞拉首都加拉加斯市发生之前，一个年轻的女大学生在西部邊境州[[塔奇拉州|塔奇拉州]]的[[聖克里斯托瓦爾_(塔奇拉州)|聖克里斯托瓦爾]]大学校园中遭遇强奸未遂，导致早已不滿在总统马杜罗和其前任总统查韦斯任內治安恶化的學生發起抗議。但是导致事态扩大的真正原因则是警方对他们最初的抗议态度恶劣，其中一些学生被涉嫌滥用权力的警察拘留，以及呼吁释放他们的后续示威活动。这些抗议活动持续扩大，吸引了非学生的参与，并导致更多的拘留事件，最终导致更多其他学生参加，而抗议活动蔓延到加拉加斯和其他城市，此时反对派领导人也介入进来。<ref name= AttemptedRape>{{cite news |url= http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Latest-News-Wires/2014/0222/Did-attempted-rape-ignite-Venezuela-s-national-protests |title= Did attempted rape ignite Venezuela's national protests? |author= Sequera, Vivia |publisher= The Christian Science Monitor |agency= Associated Press |date= 2014-02-22 |accessdate= 2014-02-24 |archive-date= 2014-02-23 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140223215253/http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Latest-News-Wires/2014/0222/Did-attempted-rape-ignite-Venezuela-s-national-protests |dead-url= no }}</ref>

马杜罗表示[[聖克里斯托瓦爾_(塔奇拉州)|聖克里斯托瓦爾]]正在被哥伦比亚前总统[[阿尔瓦罗·乌里韦·贝莱斯|阿尔瓦罗·乌里韦·贝莱斯]]率领的右翼的[[准军事部队|准军事部队]]包围；乌里韦驳回了这种说法，表示这是一种分心战术。马杜罗还指出，克里斯托瓦尔市市长丹尼尔·塞瓦略斯，同作为莱奥波尔多·洛佩斯的一员，将会因煽动暴力被判刑。<ref name=AttemptedRape/>

洛佩斯是反政府的领军人物。<ref>{{cite news|last=López|first=Virgina|title=Venezuelans on streets again as protest leader awaits trial|url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/feb/22/venezuelans-streets-protest-leader|accessdate=22 February 2014|newspaper=The Guardian|date=22 February 2014|archive-date=2014-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303223618/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/feb/22/venezuelans-streets-protest-leader|dead-url=no}}</ref>在{{link-en|2002年委内瑞拉政变计划|2002 Venezuelan coup d'état attempt}}的周围事件中，洛佩斯“精心策划公开抗议反对查韦斯，并在公民逮捕查韦斯的内政部长中发挥核心作用”，{{link-en|拉蒙·罗德里格斯|Ramón Rodríguez Chacín}}说道，虽然他后来试图让自己远离这场事件，<ref>{{cite web |author= Peralta, Eyder |date= 20 February 2013 |url= http://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2014/02/20/280207441/5-things-to-know-about-venezuelas-protest-leader |title= 5 Things To Know About Venezuela's Protest Leader |publisher= NPR |accessdate= 2014-02-23 |archive-date= 2014-02-21 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140221075204/http://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2014/02/20/280207441/5-things-to-know-about-venezuelas-protest-leader |dead-url= no }}</ref>且并未签署{{link-en|卡莫纳法令|Carmona Decree}}。<ref name=Lightning>{{cite news|author=Kraul, Chris|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2006/jul/19/world/fg-venezuela19|title=A Lightning Rod for Venezuela's Political Strife|work=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|date=2006-07-19|accessdate=2018-03-02|archive-date=2017-12-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171219220039/http://articles.latimes.com/2006/jul/19/world/fg-venezuela19|dead-url=no}} Also [http://venezuelareal.zoomblog.com/archivo/2006/07/20/a-Lightning-Rod-for-Venezuelas-Politic.html online here.] {{Wayback|url=http://venezuelareal.zoomblog.com/archivo/2006/07/20/a-Lightning-Rod-for-Venezuelas-Politic.html |date=20140222004300 }}</ref>委内瑞拉政府禁止洛佩斯拥有当选资格被{{link-en|美洲人权法院|Inter-American Court of Human Rights}}裁定为非法，但委内瑞拉政府拒绝遵守法院的裁决。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.economist.com/news/americas/21596945-after-opposition-leader-arrested-violence-continues-unabated-tale-two-prisoners|accessdate=23 February 2014|title=Protests in Venezuela: A tale of two prisoners|work=[[The_Economist|The Economist]]|archive-date=2014-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302223102/http://www.economist.com/news/americas/21596945-after-opposition-leader-arrested-violence-continues-unabated-tale-two-prisoners|dead-url=no}}</ref>洛佩斯曾被美国外交官尊重。<ref>{{cite news|script-title=en:‘Volcano of Energy’ Lopez Who Rode Shot Car Roils Venezuela|url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-02-22/-volcano-of-energy-lopez-who-rode-shot-car-roils-venezuela-2-.html|accessdate=22 February 2014|newspaper=Bloomberg|date=22 February 2014|archive-date=2014-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140304113121/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-02-22/-volcano-of-energy-lopez-who-rode-shot-car-roils-venezuela-2-.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 腐败 ===
{{main|委内瑞拉的腐败}}
委内瑞拉的贪污腐败相比[[贪污感知指数|世界标准]]有着较高的系数。腐败是很难可靠地计算的，而是一个被大众所知晓的[[贪污感知指数|贪污感知指数]]是每年由柏林的非政府组织[[透明国际|透明国际]]（TNI）所统计的。委内瑞拉在TNI的调查中一直是最腐败的国家之一，因为他们从1995年开始，排名处于41个统计国家的38名<ref>''[[Transparency_International|Transparency International]]'', 15 July 1995, [http://www.transparency.org/content/download/2915/18031/file/cpi1995.pdf 1995 TI Corruption Index] {{Wayback|url=http://www.transparency.org/content/download/2915/18031/file/cpi1995.pdf |date=20100903144412 }}</ref>并在随后的几年中同样严重（如在2008年位于180个国家的第158位），在美洲属于除了[[海地|海地]]外最糟糕的国家<ref>''[[Transparency_International|Transparency International]]'', [http://www.transparency.org/news_room/in_focus/2008/cpi2008/cpi_2008_table 2008 Corruption Perceptions Index] {{Wayback|url=http://www.transparency.org/news_room/in_focus/2008/cpi2008/cpi_2008_table |date=20090311002755 }}, accessed 30 June 2009</ref>，在2012年属于全球最腐败的10个国家之倒数行列排名176个国家的165名（位于[[布隆迪|布隆迪]]、[[乍得|乍得]]及[[海地|海地]]之后<ref name=2012Index>{{cite news|title=Factbox: Transparency International's global corruption index|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/12/05/us-corruption-transparency-global-idUSBRE8B406G20121205|accessdate=5 December 2012|newspaper=Reuters|date=5 December 2012|archive-date=2014-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302135330/http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/12/05/us-corruption-transparency-global-idUSBRE8B406G20121205|dead-url=yes}}</ref>）。TNI发布的数据表明，大多数委内瑞拉人认为政府的反腐败努力是没有成果的，腐败现象在政府机构，如司法制度、议会、立法机关和警察尤甚。<ref>{{cite web|title=GLOBAL CORRUPTION BAROMETER 2010/11|url=http://www.transparency.org/country#VEN_PublicOpinion|publisher=Transparency International|accessdate=26 February 2014|archive-date=2019-05-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524182350/https://www.transparency.org/country#VEN_PublicOpinion|dead-url=no}}</ref>根据TNI的调查，委内瑞拉目前在世界上跻身前20个最腐败的国家，排名地17（160/177），其司法系统已被世界公认为是最腐败的。<ref>{{cite web|title=CORRUPTION BY COUNTRY / TERRITORY: VENEZUELA|url=http://www.transparency.org/country#VEN|publisher=Transparency International|accessdate=26 February 2014|archive-date=2019-05-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524182350/https://www.transparency.org/country#VEN|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===经济问题===
{{main|委内瑞拉经济}}
[[File:Marcha_hacia_el_Palacio_de_Justicia_de_Maracaibo_-_Venezuela_16.jpg|250px]]
委内瑞拉政府的经济政策，如严格的价格管制。这些政策导致了国内相比世界其他地方有着高通货膨胀率以及食品和其他商品的严重短缺。<ref name="economist.com"/>而马杜罗总统指责反对他的人的目的是发动“经济战”，特别指责乃资本主义以及[[炒作|炒作]]。<ref name="Edition.cnn.com"/>

在2013年，委内瑞拉货币贬值<ref>{{elucidate|date=February 2014}}{{cite news|title=Venezuela Slashes Currency Value|url=http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424127887323951904578292383059267360|accessdate=14 December 2013|newspaper=Wall Street Journal|date=9 February 2013|archive-date=2013-12-01|archive-url=https://archive.today/20131201045424/http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424127887323951904578292383059267360|dead-url=no}}</ref>，必需品如卫生纸、牛奶和面粉持续短缺。<ref>{{cite news|last=Lopez|first=Virginia|title=Venezuela food shortages: 'No one can explain why a rich country has no food'|url=http://www.theguardian.com/global-development/poverty-matters/2013/sep/26/venezuela-food-shortages-rich-country-cia|accessdate=14 December 2013|newspaper=The Guardian|date=26 September 2013|archive-date=2014-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303101143/http://www.theguardian.com/global-development/poverty-matters/2013/sep/26/venezuela-food-shortages-rich-country-cia|dead-url=no}}</ref>而这灾难性的货币政策意味着企业无法进口必须商品如纸，<ref name="The party is over">{{cite news|title=The party is over|accessdate=22 February 2014|newspaper=The Economist|date=1 February 2014}}</ref>而政府占用了全国最大的卫生纸制造商Manpa，目的是检查“可分流分布”和“非法经营”。<ref>{{cite news|last=Mogollon|first=Mery|title=Venezuela seizes another asset: Toilet paper factory|url=http://www.latimes.com/world/worldnow/la-fg-wn-venezuela-seizes-another-asset-toilet-paper-factory-20130921,0,1089056.story|accessdate=19 February 2014|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|date=21 September 2013|archive-date=2014-04-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140421095526/http://www.latimes.com/world/worldnow/la-fg-wn-venezuela-seizes-another-asset-toilet-paper-factory-20130921,0,1089056.story|dead-url=no}}</ref>政府正在使用强势通货来支付账单。委内瑞拉最大的私人拥有的食品生产商企业Empresas Polar还欠政府$4.63亿债务，因为它无法支付国外供应商处于生产停滞状态。<ref name="The party is over"/>

2013年11月，也就是地方选举的前周，马杜罗下令军方接管家电卖场，有分析师认为此举是“自相残杀式”经济方针，使未来商品更加短缺。<ref>{{cite news|title=Maduro's crackdown on appliance stores may win key votes, but spurs uncertainty in Venezuela|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2013/11/13/maduro-crackdown-on-appliance-stores-may-win-key-votes-but-spurs-uncertainty-in/|accessdate=19 February 2014|newspaper=Fox News|date=13 November 2013|archive-date=2014-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140304122750/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2013/11/13/maduro-crackdown-on-appliance-stores-may-win-key-votes-but-spurs-uncertainty-in/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Lopez|first=Virginia|title=Venezuelans muse on economic woes that make milk scarce but fridges a steal|url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/nov/15/venezuela-economy-maduro-oil-dollar-corruption|accessdate=19 February 2014|newspaper=The Guardian|date=15 November 2013|archive-date=2014-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227185037/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/nov/15/venezuela-economy-maduro-oil-dollar-corruption|dead-url=no}}</ref>马杜罗说，他是针对“经济战”和为买家执行“公平”的价格，称“这是为国家的利益，没有货物留在仓库与货架上”。<ref>{{cite news|title=Venezuela sends in troops to force electronics chain to charge 'fair' prices|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/venezuela-sends-troops-force-electronics-chain-charge-fair-prices-v21399541|accessdate=19 February 2014|newspaper=NBC News|archive-date=2014-02-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221163442/http://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/venezuela-sends-troops-force-electronics-chain-charge-fair-prices-v21399541|dead-url=no}}</ref>然而[[价格管制|价格管制]]使企业遭受损失，并导致商品短缺、排长队、抢，甚至被国民警卫队人员哄抢。<ref>{{cite news|title=Venezuela’s "economic war"|accessdate=22 February 2014|newspaper=The Economist|date=16 November 2013}}</ref>

2014年2月，政府表示已查处了超过3500吨违禁品与运往哥伦比亚的食品和燃料，本意为打击边境的“走私”或“投机”。国会主席表示：“所有的这些食物应分配给委内瑞拉人民，而不是在这些歹徒手里”。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.el-nacional.com/politica/Cabello-especial-organismos-seguridad-Apure_0_351565090.html |title=Cabello en Apure: Decomisamos 12.000 litros de aceites y 30 toneladas de arroz |publisher=El-nacional.com |date= |accessdate=21 February 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224203551/http://www.el-nacional.com/politica/Cabello-especial-organismos-seguridad-Apure_0_351565090.html |archivedate=2014年2月24日 }}</ref>

2月21日，加拉加斯大学医院医生罢工，由于物资缺乏，即使近3000人需要手术治疗也无从手术。<ref>{{cite news|title=Médicos del Hospital Universitario de Caracas suspenden cirugías por falta de insumos|url=http://globovision.com/articulo/medicos-del-hospital-universitario-paralizan-procedimientos-quirurgicos-tras-falta-de-insumos|accessdate=21 February 2014|newspaper=Globovision|date=21 February 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228074857/http://globovision.com/articulo/medicos-del-hospital-universitario-paralizan-procedimientos-quirurgicos-tras-falta-de-insumos|archivedate=2014年2月28日}}</ref>政府的货币政策已难以进口药品和其他医疗用品。<ref>{{cite news|title=Latin America’s weakest economies are reaching breaking-point|accessdate=22 February 2014|newspaper=Economist|date=1 February 2014}}</ref>政府没有提供足够的美元用于医疗用品，他们的水平还停滞在2010年时期。<ref>{{cite news|title=Doctors say Venezuela's health care in collapse|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/doctors-say-venezuelas-health-care-collapse|accessdate=22 February 2014|newspaper=Associated Press|archive-date=2014-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140226055123/http://bigstory.ap.org/article/doctors-say-venezuelas-health-care-collapse|dead-url=no}}</ref>

为应对通胀马杜罗已经提高了最低工资标准、法定最低全职工人和养老金，以官方通货膨胀率同样的百分比：在2013年5月至2014年1月间的59％。<ref>{{cite news|last=Vyas|first=Kejal|title=Venezuela Raises Minimum Wage, Pension Benefits Amid High Inflation|url=http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702304617404579304872708948150|newspaper=Wall Street Journal|date=6 January 2014|accessdate=2014-03-04|archive-date=2014-02-19|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140219095754/http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702304617404579304872708948150|dead-url=no}}</ref>实际通胀率可能要高得多，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://qz.com/180390/venezuelas-real-inflation-may-be-six-times-the-official-rate/ |title=Venezuela’s real inflation may be six times the official rate |publisher=Quartz |accessdate=25 February 2014 |archive-date=2014-03-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302222238/http://qz.com/180390/venezuelas-real-inflation-may-be-six-times-the-official-rate/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>且[[货币供给|货币供给]]量持续增加。<ref>{{cite web|title=Monetary aggregates rising sharply|url=http://www.eiu.com/industry/article/711546455/monetary-aggregates-rising-sharply/2014-02-17|publisher=Economist Intelligence Unit|accessdate=25 February 2014|archive-date=2014-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228163204/http://www.eiu.com/industry/article/711546455/monetary-aggregates-rising-sharply/2014-02-17|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 犯罪率 ===
{{main|委内瑞拉的犯罪}}
[[File:Protestor_with_Sign_2014_Venezuela.png|170px]]
2014年1月前女演员及[[委内瑞拉小姐|委内瑞拉小姐]]得主[[莫尼卡·斯皮尔·莫茨|莫尼卡·斯皮尔·莫茨]]以及她丈夫带她们五六岁大的女儿出门购物时遭遇抢劫并罹难，他们的女儿腿部受伤但生命无危险，<ref name=MostDangerous/>委内瑞拉被[[第四台_(英國)|英国第四台]]形容为“世界上的一个最危险的国家”：<ref name=MostDangerous/>“在[[乌戈·查韦斯|乌戈·查韦斯]]执政期间谋杀和武装抢劫事件持续升级。”<ref name=MostDangerous/>犯罪洞察组织将不断升级的暴力归因于“高层的腐败、警察部队缺乏投资和孱弱的枪支管制”。<ref name=MostDangerous/>

在委内瑞拉，每21分钟就有一个人被谋杀。<ref>{{cite news|title=Seven Things To Know About the Venezuela Crisis|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/venezuela-crisis/seven-things-know-about-venezuela-crisis-n38556|accessdate=26 February 2014|newspaper=NBC News|date=25 February 2014|archive-date=2014-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303003431/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/venezuela-crisis/seven-things-know-about-venezuela-crisis-n38556|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Castillo|first=Mariano|title=Beauty queen's killers nabbed, Venezuela says|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/01/09/world/americas/monica-spear-venezuela-beauty-queen-killed/|accessdate=26 February 2014|newspaper=CNN|date=9 January 2014|archive-date=2014-02-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221100911/http://www.cnn.com/2014/01/09/world/americas/monica-spear-venezuela-beauty-queen-killed/|dead-url=no}}</ref>委内瑞拉暴力观察站声称，该国的谋杀率是每10万人中有近80人死于谋杀，而政府统计数据把它定于每10万中39人死于谋杀。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2014/01/09/world/americas/monica-spear-venezuela-beauty-queen-killed/ |title=Beauty queen Monica Spear's killers nabbed, Venezuela says - CNN.com |publisher=Edition.cnn.com |date=10 January 2014 |accessdate=21 February 2014 |archive-date=2014-02-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227112012/http://edition.cnn.com/2014/01/09/world/americas/monica-spear-venezuela-beauty-queen-killed/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>政府宣称，这些谋杀案的72％发生于药品竞争团伙和委内瑞拉代号为“Plan Patria Segura（国土安全计划）”的打击犯罪行动之间，根据政府声称，在2013年绑架和谋杀案数据少于51％，相比2012年减少17％。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vtv.gob.ve/articulos/2013/12/22/gobierno-ha-logrado-reducir-el-secuestro-y-el-homicidio-en-51-7-y-17-5925.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2014-03-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031164947/http://www.vtv.gob.ve/articulos/2013/12/22/gobierno-ha-logrado-reducir-el-secuestro-y-el-homicidio-en-51-7-y-17-5925.html |archivedate=2014-10-31 }}</ref>

反对派说，犯罪率高是政府所造成的。“为了软化政治和司法机构的犯罪，并在公共范围内美化犯罪”，而按政府的说法“资本主义”是罪魁祸首，尽管贫困水平总体下降，且资本主义已经失去了其在该国的地位。<ref>{{cite news|title=Venezuela's violent crime fuels the death business|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/02/20/us-venezuela-crime-idUSBREA1J0KM20140220|accessdate=4 March 2014|newspaper=Reuters|date=20 February 2014|archive-date=2014-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140401043711/http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/02/20/us-venezuela-crime-idUSBREA1J0KM20140220|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

而[[美国国务院|美国国务院]]和[[加拿大政府|加拿大政府]]曾警告外国游客，他们可能会在当地受到[[抢劫|抢劫]]、所要[[赎金|赎金]]的[[绑架|绑架]]或被恐怖组织挟持以及[[谋杀|谋杀]]。<ref>{{cite web|title=Venezuela Travel Warning|url=http://travel.state.gov/content/passports/english/alertswarnings/venezuela-travel-warning.html|publisher=United States Department of State|accessdate=9 February 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140130073159/http://travel.state.gov/content/passports/english/alertswarnings/venezuela-travel-warning.html|archivedate=2014年1月30日}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Venezuela|url=http://travel.gc.ca/destinations/venezuela|publisher=Government of Canada|accessdate=9 February 2014|archive-date=2019-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501072806/https://travel.gc.ca/destinations/venezuela|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[英国|英国]]的[[外交及联邦事务部|外交及联邦事务部]]曾表示反对在哥伦比亚边境的苏利亚、塔奇拉和阿普雷州80公里（50英里）内的所有旅游活动。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/venezuela |title=Venezuela travel advice |publisher=GOV.UK |date=18 December 2013 |accessdate=21 February 2014 |archive-date=2017-08-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808091916/https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/venezuela |dead-url=no }}</ref>

===选举===
{{main|2013年委内瑞拉总统选举}}
[[File:2014_Carnaval_Maduro_Signs.jpg|250px]]中许多[[尼古拉斯·马杜罗|尼古拉斯·马杜罗]]的宣传招牌。]]
2013年4月14日尼古拉斯·马杜罗以1.5％优势领先第二候选人卡普利莱斯·拉东斯基赢得总统选举。这次选举被指责作弊。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/venezuelan-president-accused-of-electoral-fraud-at-home-finds-backing-abroad/2013/05/10/15d607d8-b9a5-11e2-b568-6917f6ac6d9d_story.html |title=Venezuelan president, accused of electoral fraud at home, finds backing abroad |publisher=The Washington Post |date=10 May 2013 |accessdate=16 February 2014 |archive-date=2014-11-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141104192143/http://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/venezuelan-president-accused-of-electoral-fraud-at-home-finds-backing-abroad/2013/05/10/15d607d8-b9a5-11e2-b568-6917f6ac6d9d_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>反对党领袖卡普利莱斯拒绝接受选举结果，声称选举行为违规，尽管选举委员会之后随机选择54％的选票进行纸张选票的重新审计，相比电子记录未发现问题。<ref name="BBC19April">{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-22220526|title=Nicolas Maduro sworn in as new Venezuelan president|work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]]|date=19 April 2013|accessdate=18 June 2013|archive-date=2016-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160124054356/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-22220526|dead-url=no}}</ref>卡普利莱斯最初呼吁其余46％的选票继续进行重审，声称这将证明他已在大选中获胜。选举委员会同意进行审核，并计划于五月开始。<ref name=BBC19April/><ref name=BBC28April>{{cite web|title=Venezuela to audit votes without opposition conditions|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-22333705|publisher=BBC|date=28 April 2013|accessdate=29 April 2013|archive-date=2013-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131020054623/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-22333705|dead-url=no}}</ref>后来卡普利莱斯改变了主意，他增加了对选举注册信息的完整的审计要求（校对并验证记录中所有的指纹和签名），并说现行的计票程序是个“笑话”，而选举委员会称这一理由“不可能”，因为要消耗以“年”为单位的时间。<ref name=BBC28April/>

2013年6月12日审计结果公布。全国选举委员会（CNE）表示，最后审计的结果与之前无异，并确认马杜罗在选举中获胜。<ref name="BBC12June">{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-22866490|title=Venezuela audit confirms Nicolas Maduro electoral victory|work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]]|date=12 June 2013|accessdate=18 June 2013|archive-date=2013-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224213347/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-22866490|dead-url=no}}</ref>CNE由五名成员组成，其中四个是由政府任命。而据第五个独立成员所说，政府的行动是“国家近代史中最不平等的时期”。<ref name="Maduro’s hollow victory">{{cite news|title=Maduro’s hollow victory|accessdate=22 February 2014|newspaper=Economist|date=14 December 2013}}</ref>而由美国前总统[[卡特|卡特]]所办的[[卡特中心|卡特中心]]则发现了问题，该中心表示问题在于通过执政党的媒体支持以及利用政府资源来支持竞选活动。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cartercenter.org/resources/pdfs/news/peace_publications/election_reports/venezuela-pre-election-rpt-2013.pdf |title=Preliminary Report Study Missision of the Carter Center : Presidential Elections in Venezuela – April 14, 2013 |publisher=Catercenter.org |accessdate=21 February 2014 |archive-date=2014-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222134242/https://www.cartercenter.org/resources/pdfs/news/peace_publications/election_reports/venezuela-pre-election-rpt-2013.pdf |dead-url=yes }}</ref>政府的资源被用来支持执政党的竞选活动；政府车辆被用于运输。而在最近的地方选举中，马杜罗每天花两小时进行电视直播，<ref name="Maduro’s hollow victory"/>而忽视了反对派候选人或对其进行侮辱。
===德政部分===
[[File:Venezuela_2011_Ameridian_population_proportion_map.png|303px]]）土著比例远低于安第斯其余国家，仅[[佩里哈山脉|佩里哈山脉]]仍是土著文化的强势区]]
1999年[[玻利瓦尔革命|玻利瓦尔革命]]前，委内瑞拉的土著权益政策远远落后于其他拉美国家，1961年宪法甚至比1947年宪法更加残害土著权益。<ref name=vancott51>Van Cott (2003), "Andean Indigenous Movements and Constitutional Transformation: Venezuela in Comparative Perspective", ''Latin American Perspectives'' 30(1), p51</ref>1999年玻利瓦尔革命时委内瑞拉已成为南美土著比例最低国家之一，梅里达山脉则属于委内瑞拉最“白”的地区之一，土著几乎灭绝殆尽。不过，委内瑞拉的玻利瓦尔政府仍然成功寻访识别出了大量土著民族。<ref>{{cite web |title=Pueblos Indígenas de Mérida resaltan su herencia cultural |url=https://www.cenditel.gob.ve/node/1450 |access-date=2022-01-01 |archive-date=2018-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180906090838/http://www.cenditel.gob.ve/node/1450 |dead-url=no }}</ref>今天，[[苏克雷市_(梅里达州)|苏克雷市]]首府[[拉古尼亚斯_(梅里达州)|拉古尼亚斯]]城Timoto–Cuica两族下的Guazábara, Quinanoque, Orkas, Mucumbu, Casés与Quinaores之部落正积极发展自己的文化，<ref>{{cite web |author1=Belkis Rojas Trejo |title=Territorio y memoria territorial sagrada entre los indígenas de Lagunillas, Mérida, Venezuela |url=http://www.saber.ula.ve/bitstream/handle/123456789/42478/articulo6.pdf?sequence=1&isAllowed=y |archiveurl=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:6EsFb_fEdcMJ:www.saber.ula.ve/bitstream/handle/123456789/42478/articulo6.pdf%3Fsequence%3D1%26isAllowed%3Dy+&cd=12&hl=zh-CN&ct=clnk&gl=us}}</ref>而不需像哥伦比亚土著[[因柯阿洼族|因柯阿洼族]]那样随时担心遭到[[杀人小队|杀人小队]]（death squad）的屠杀。因此委内瑞拉国内也依然存在大量亲政府示威者。

==暴力抗议==
===集体党===
名为“集体党”（Colectivos）的武装组织，遭到[[查韦斯|查韦斯]]指责干预其政府后，公然袭击示威者和反对派电视台的工作人员，向记者发送死亡威胁，向[[梵蒂冈|梵蒂冈]]特使发射催泪瓦斯<ref name="reuters colectivo">{{cite news|last=Wallis|first=Daniel|title=Venezuela violence puts focus on militant 'colectivo' groups|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/02/13/venezuela-protests-colectivos-idUSL2N0LI14W20140213|accessdate=22 February 2014|newspaper=Reuters|date=13 February 2014|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924193514/http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/02/13/venezuela-protests-colectivos-idUSL2N0LI14W20140213|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。[[人权观察组织|人权观察组织]]表示，“委内瑞拉政府容忍促进平民武装组织”，让他们“恐吓示威者，发动暴力事件”<ref name=HRWcolectivo>{{cite web|title=Venezuela: Violence Against Protesters, Journalists|url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2014/02/21/venezuela-violence-against-protesters-journalists|publisher=Human Rights Watch|accessdate=21 March 2014|archive-date=2014-02-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221210347/http://www.hrw.org/news/2014/02/21/venezuela-violence-against-protesters-journalists|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[社会党国际|社会党国际]]同时谴责让袭击示威者的非正规团体逍遥法外的行为<ref name=SIendtoviolence>{{cite web|title=Venezuela : for an end to the violence|url=http://www.socialistinternational.org/viewArticle.cfm?ArticleID=2284|publisher=Socialist International|accessdate=2014-05-15|archive-date=2014-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140517152806/http://www.socialistinternational.org/viewArticle.cfm?ArticleID=2284|dead-url=no}}</ref>。马杜罗总统感谢摩托车骑士党协助反击他所认为的“极端右翼组织发起的法西斯争辩”，同时也让武装组织疏远自己，声称他们“无用武之地<ref name=USAcolectivo>{{cite news|title=Protesters back in streets in Venezuela|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2014/02/24/ex-venezuelan-general-standoff/5772237/|accessdate=21 March 2014|newspaper=USA Today|date=24 February 2014|archive-date=2014-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141019000154/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2014/02/24/ex-venezuelan-general-standoff/5772237/|dead-url=no}}</ref>”。日后有机会，马杜罗总统对所有暴力团伙表示谴责，并表示政府支持者若犯法，会像反对派支持者那样去坐牢。他表示，暴力人士跟政府支持者同样没有用武之地，需要立即退出亲政府运动<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web|title=Maduro no aceptará grupos violentos y armados en el chavismo y advierte que podrian ir a la carcel|url=http://www.noticias24.com/venezuela/noticia/222386/maduro-no-aceptara-grupos-violentos-y-armados-en-el-chavismo-y-advierte-que-podrian-ir-a-la-carcel/|publisher=Noticias21|accessdate=17 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141209001056/http://www.noticias24.com/venezuela/noticia/222386/maduro-no-aceptara-grupos-violentos-y-armados-en-el-chavismo-y-advierte-que-podrian-ir-a-la-carcel/|archive-date=2014-12-09|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

某些“集体党”份子的暴力行为，没有受到委内瑞拉政府军的阻碍<ref name="lapatilla.com">{{cite news|title=Colectivos de paz accionan armas de fuego en la Rómulo Gallegos ante mirada de la GNB|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2014/02/19/colectivos-de-paz-accionan-armas-de-fuego-en-la-romulo-gallegos-ante-mirada-de-la-gnb/|accessdate=19 February 2014|newspaper=La Patilla|date=19 February 2014|archive-date=2017-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171010121724/https://www.lapatilla.com/site/2014/02/19/colectivos-de-paz-accionan-armas-de-fuego-en-la-romulo-gallegos-ante-mirada-de-la-gnb/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他们的数辆卡车涉嫌袭击一幢用于抗议的公寓大楼，破坏五辆汽车，烧毁2辆，并朝公寓内开火，造成一人受伤<ref name= IMPULSOcolectivo>{{cite news|title=#16A Una persona herida y dos vehículos quemados fue el saldo de ataque de colectivos en urbanización Río Lama|url=http://elimpulso.com/articulo/16a-queman-dos-carros-esta-madrugada-en-urbanizacion-rio-lama#|accessdate=16 April 2014|newspaper=El Impulso|date=16 April 2014|archive-date=2014-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141222103253/http://elimpulso.com/articulo/16a-queman-dos-carros-esta-madrugada-en-urbanizacion-rio-lama|dead-url=no}}</ref>。Televen一名记者表示，武装团体在[[马拉开波|马拉开波]]的公寓楼内试图绑架和强奸个人，未见国民警卫队的干预<ref>{{cite news|title=Impactante video del horror vivido por una mujer en Maracaibo: grupos violentos amenazaron con violarla|url=http://www.canalntn24.com/videos/belinda-alvarado-denuncia-que-grupos-violentos-entraron-su-casa-e-intentaron-ultrajarla-126463|accessdate=29 April 2014|newspaper=NTN24|date=27 March 2014|archive-date=2014-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204115937/http://www.canalntn24.com/videos/belinda-alvarado-denuncia-que-grupos-violentos-entraron-su-casa-e-intentaron-ultrajarla-126463|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=En Maracaibo: amenazas de violación, saqueo de viviendas y vehículos quemados bajo la mirada pasiva de la GNB|url=http://m.ntn24.com/article.php?url=/node/126431|accessdate=29 April 2014|newspaper=NTN24|date=27 March 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429050612/http://m.ntn24.com/article.php?url=%2Fnode%2F126431|archivedate=2014年4月29日}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title="Colectivos" intentaron secuestrar a mujer en Palaima|url=http://www.elpropio.com/actualidad/Denuncian-colectivos-intentaron-residencias-marabinas_0_489551109.html|accessdate=29 April 2014|newspaper=El Propio|date=27 March 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429050208/http://www.elpropio.com/actualidad/Denuncian-colectivos-intentaron-residencias-marabinas_0_489551109.html|archivedate=2014年4月29日}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Colectivos paramilitares irrumpen en hogares y amenazan con violar a los residentes con "permiso" de la GNB|url=http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2014/03/27/colectivos-paramilitares-irrumpen-en-hogares-y-amenazan-con-violar-a-los-residentes-con-permiso-de-la-gnb/|accessdate=29 March 2014|newspaper=La Patilla|date=27 March 2014|archive-date=2017-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811221930/http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2014/03/27/colectivos-paramilitares-irrumpen-en-hogares-y-amenazan-con-violar-a-los-residentes-con-permiso-de-la-gnb/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。委内瑞拉副总统[[豪尔赫·阿雷亚萨|豪尔赫·阿雷亚萨]]称赞集体党的行为，表示“如果集体党机车党的行为称得上模范的话，那么它就是[[玻利瓦尔革命|玻利瓦尔革命]]<ref name=APcolectivo>{{cite news|title=Armed pro-govt militias roil Venezuela protests|url=http://hosted2.ap.org/APDEFAULT/cae69a7523db45408eeb2b3a98c0c9c5/Article_2014-03-30-Venezuela-Loyalist%20Militias/id-ea31fc1b693a498da7c38a8a2ac41b22|accessdate=31 March 2014|newspaper=The Associated Press|date=30 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205105816/http://hosted2.ap.org/APDEFAULT/cae69a7523db45408eeb2b3a98c0c9c5/Article_2014-03-30-Venezuela-Loyalist%20Militias/id-ea31fc1b693a498da7c38a8a2ac41b22|archive-date=2014-12-05|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。”然而于3月28日，阿雷亚萨承诺政府将取缔国家的所有非正规武装团体<ref>{{cite news|title=Arreaza promete desarme de grupos armados|url=http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/140328/arre